https://github.com/lzap/systemd-shortcuts

take time to study systemd and other community cheatsheets as well

# show systemd service file:
systemctl cat dhcpcd.service

# systemd-analyze plot : units that take a long time to start:
systemd-analyze plot > plot.svg

# get log for a service, -b for current boot:
journalctl -u zookeeper.service -b

# Look for errors in the log files located at /var/log, as well as high priority errors in the systemd journal:
journalctl -p 3 -b
systemctl --failed

